# Java Backend Rules

## Language & Framework
- Java 17 with Spring Boot 3.2
- Use Java 17 features: records, text blocks, pattern matching, sealed classes
- H2 in-memory database with JPA/Hibernate

## Dependency Injection
- Use constructor injection (not @Autowired on fields)
- Mark dependencies as final

## Controllers
- Return ResponseEntity<T> from all endpoints
- Use @PathVariable and @RequestParam with descriptive names
- Add @Valid for request body validation
- Follow REST naming conventions (/api/resource, plural nouns)

## Services
- Keep services thin — business logic only
- Use @Transactional for write operations
- Throw specific exceptions (ResourceNotFoundException, IllegalArgumentException)
- Never return null — use Optional or throw

## Error Handling
- Use the GlobalExceptionHandler for consistent error responses
- Error messages must be descriptive and user-friendly
- Never expose stack traces to the client

## Testing
- Use @SpringBootTest + @AutoConfigureMockMvc for integration tests
- Use descriptive test method names: shouldDoSomethingWhenCondition()
- Test happy path, error cases, and edge cases
